vulnerability.name: USN-5008-2
vulnerability.description: USN-5008-1 fixed a vulnerability in avahi. This update provides the corresponding update for Ubuntu 14.04 ESM and Ubuntu 16.04 ESM.  Original advisory details:   Thomas Kremer discovered that Avahi incorrectly handled termination signals  on the Unix socket. A local attacker could possibly use this issue to cause  Avahi to hang, resulting in a denial of service.

statements.status_notes: Avahi could be made to denial of service if it received a specially crafted input. Available with Ubuntu Pro.
